description: Incheon Municipal Museum is a historical and artistic museum with local history as its exhibition content. Opened in 1946, the Incheon Metropolitan Municipal Museum is a museum with a long history. The historically important objects of Korea from the Stone Age to modern times are displayed here. It features special exhibitions throughout the year and also regularly hosts cultural performances. In the curated exhibition hall on the second floor of the museum, there are sometimes exhibitions of exchanges with other cities.
